<subSubSection id="9B17EDD201B2D18385931FB0D5C152BA" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" type="reference_group">
<paragraph id="7364B9AC4C51E1BF74020F13F5AA88F8" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName id="BA64876D59DBEEA69D65883034667053" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amblyolepis">Vernonia amblyolepis</taxonomicName>
Baker, Bull. Misc. Inf. Kew 1898: 146 (1898). Type: Malawi, Nyika Plateau, 
<emphasis id="FC8476B2095E87004A83510B1EFF1AFB" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Whyte 204</emphasis>
(Lechtotype designated here, K, scanned image at US!), Mpata to Nyasa-Tanganyika Plateau, 
<emphasis id="7A33CE87F0780E023D0DD277FAD01ED1" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Whyte s.n.</emphasis>
(isolectotype, K, scanned image at US!). The two specimens at K are labeled as syntypes. The Whyte 204 was selected as the lectotype because it is numbered.
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="F8AC2F7180FFBB2B2B03FF963AE6C6B4" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName id="E244E14097AB70DF00568DD9155D3B76" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pratensis">Vernonia pratensis</taxonomicName>
Hiern, Cat. Afr. Pl. Welw. 1: 523 (1898) homonym illeg., non Klatt 1892 nec Drake 1897. Type: Angola, 
<emphasis id="C5830E5B6929213EFFF278A3A3903338" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Welwitsch 3364</emphasis>
(isotype K).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="27C98AA2EB7BD44FEA13590B4D2522D3" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName id="248D66C3725C8EBAD49B94CD8D5F1519" authorityName="Muschl" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandtii">Vernonia kandtii</taxonomicName>
Muschl., Bot. Jahrb. Syst. 46: 87 (1911). Type: Rwanda, Niansa, 
<emphasis id="C4AD4DE8C46B3910161EA3D4A1719C62" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Kandt 69</emphasis>
(holotype B, destroyed, isotype EA).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8EA9E271A8628A11CEEBE5F5E74016C2" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<taxonomicName id="8E014261CFD19C5ADEF836C10B162657" authorityName="H. Wild" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exasperata">Vernonia exasperata</taxonomicName>
H. Wild, Kirkia 11: 12 (1978), nom. nov. for 
<taxonomicName id="DF3FB89C885DFF5BEC8748A90B044D26" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="pratensis">
<emphasis id="2554961C98BCF93F8F721BCF71E27D0E" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Vernonia pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hiern.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="E7BDD5ECF29B5199476F90BB7C688FD0" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" type="distribution">
<paragraph id="DF6A846AD4A81DB78E572B8E0D005BAD" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Distribution.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="759DF81A75042519FAE5F5CCE0BD4DFD" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">The species is known from Angola, Malawi, Rwanda and Tanzania.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="95E242A0209EEAEA5861164E4D4B71F2" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" type="specimens examined">
<paragraph id="31AF7701911B3C6729CE86C9C84D528D" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Specimens Examined.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="34208A80A845B38DC47368161D4F7D4F" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<emphasis id="95E484816114BC8D0E06A926B9B9D084" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Malawi.</emphasis>
Zomba District: Zomba Plateau, top of hillside above KuChawe Inn, on grassy slope, 
<geoCoordinate id="4B852A9FE56085C5DC1E7E5D9FEA1807" degrees="15" direction="south" minutes="20" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-15.333333">15°20'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="7DEADA1C3E39D88DEC14F7602041140F" degrees="35" direction="east" minutes="18" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="35.3">35°18'E</geoCoordinate>
, 5500 ft., 14 Apr 1984, Christenson 1461 (US). Zomba District: Zomba Plateau, on upper road from KuChawe Inn downward to Zomba, near horse paddock, 
<geoCoordinate id="68941C4259F9286208580FE607F0CE5D" degrees="15" direction="south" minutes="20" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-15.333333">15°20'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="71CF77E7500183CD31344933BE3FAD86" degrees="35" direction="east" minutes="18" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="35.3">35°18'E</geoCoordinate>
, 5000 ft., 25 Apr 1984, Christenson and Lipende 1488(US). 
<emphasis id="2936E0FB3499A837B7325D34AA46F316" bold="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Uganda.</emphasis>
Buhweju County: District West Ankole, Nyarwambu River, 
<geoCoordinate id="09430C17E55632FF124E306508F465FF" degrees="0" direction="south" minutes="22" orientation="latitude" precision="925" value="-0.36666667">0°22'S</geoCoordinate>
, 
<geoCoordinate id="0CCC94011FFF024307DCAB45ABA8F227" degrees="30" direction="east" minutes="28" orientation="longitude" precision="925" value="30.466667">30°28'E</geoCoordinate>
, 1550 m, 23 Aug 1982, Rwaburindora 919(MO, US).
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection id="6A1A3982B8419E4610AFD355068BE7AF" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" type="unrecognized taxa">
<paragraph id="77CBEB52755BCE40052B165D0DB6B5F0" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Unrecognized taxa.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="C9CBD6580CC7E11D8DC1B2B603527EE0" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<bibRefCitation id="640E2BE7697081D2F6E58920339C7C64" author="Jeffrey, C" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="195 - 277" refId="B6" refString="Jeffrey, C, 1988. The Vernonieae in east tropical Africa,Notes on Compositae: V. Kew Bulletin 43: 195 - 277" title="The Vernonieae in east tropical Africa, Notes on Compositae: V." volume="43" year="1988">Jeffrey (1988)</bibRefCitation>
treated 
<taxonomicName id="A0013530CD7189186BFD7C695D88F63B" authorityName="Muschl" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandtii">
<emphasis id="274E927D9B624BD9EF40593B387C71DD" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Vernonia kandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
as a separate species that included 
<taxonomicName id="5AD502C95D5806048AFD36E75F0B951B" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="Veronia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="" order="Asterales" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="pratensis">
<emphasis id="AA14804499B582E4D30294C791FA36BA" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Veronia pratensis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
Hiern and 
<taxonomicName id="7FB45B5752A8E2F95E7C7D86BB0E08AF" authorityName="H. Wild" authorityYear="1978" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="exasperata">
<emphasis id="F4BA84E59019765DE2F1675B0DFDCA43" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">V. exasperata</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
H. Wild in its synonymy. 
<taxonomicName id="D2ECD63F0A8BE3EC43379D63CE215D65" authorityName="Muschl" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandtii">
<emphasis id="521E664B9C567F7181071AA02BBB5E2B" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Vernonia kandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is separated by 
<bibRefCitation id="23184F7265B8FAF67E14C104C6D59F0B" author="Jeffrey, C" journalOrPublisher="Kew Bulletin" pageId="6" pageNumber="27" pagination="195 - 277" refId="B6" refString="Jeffrey, C, 1988. The Vernonieae in east tropical Africa,Notes on Compositae: V. Kew Bulletin 43: 195 - 277" title="The Vernonieae in east tropical Africa, Notes on Compositae: V." volume="43" year="1988">Jeffrey (1988)</bibRefCitation>
, with some doubt, by his couplet 106 as follows:
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="452F21482E8D3041878A3A1FB6D4A543" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<table id="808DD1767A5D9A4A51880CF251A826D3" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<tr id="2B0D6D3BD0E6D1D3B505892B85AA137F" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<td id="C4EEAD143D3E91AB2A0E259A0D6C038F" isEmpty="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">-</td>
<td id="BD429B98F383F2469CDBFB00D493729C" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Inflorescence copious, with a number of branches arising from the uppermost leaf-axils; ultimate peduncles short, so that the capitula appear to be in clusters</td>
<td id="45ABE19EBC139C2704AF60FBEBD49B2E" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
62. 
<taxonomicName id="985C907B7FBA89BD9097F02764971477" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="amblyolepis">
<emphasis id="368156AA217DD974CC8A1BF73A380450" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Vernonia amblyolepis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</td>
</tr>
<tr id="1017129AF41D84A8F997080AEB5C1312" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
<td id="5C2AF878D6C34DDDE08908030E94B74B" isEmpty="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">-</td>
<td id="3E343C0AA3F927DF66BE50441460ADC8" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Inflorescence strictly terminal, few-headed, lax, the ultimate peduncles longer, so that the capitula do not appear to be in clusters</td>
<td id="48984C6089858CCA112A2483324BF577" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
61. 
<taxonomicName id="F8DB4034AC68F81E4B9391FAB71AC57E" authorityName="Muschl" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandtii">
<emphasis id="4427BF31996B8F0D87BFE89BF6378E9C" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Vernonia kandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="4AE19C7B0EC04FE481402704E02BCB94" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">
The specimens from Malawi and Uganda that were examined for this study show variation in the structure of the inflorescence and therefore, do not support a separate species status for 
<taxonomicName id="B2679FE3C533E8C247A218D5217CDF34" authorityName="Muschl" authorityYear="1911" class="Insecta" family="Philopteridae" genus="Vernonia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" lsidName="" order="Phthiraptera" pageId="5" pageNumber="26" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kandtii">
<emphasis id="37698D84AE9A1FF0352D05FAFD9D8313" italics="true" pageId="5" pageNumber="26">Vernonia kandtii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
